  "description": "The tensor product in a [monoidal category](./monoidal-category.md) is a bifunctor ⊗: C × C → C that combines two objects into one. It is the categorical analogue of multiplication: just as a [monoid](../../../../algebra/terms/monoid.md) has a binary operation on elements, a monoidal category has a binary operation on objects.",
